/* 
CSS - Cascading Style Sheets
    - apply style to html pages

  structure
    selector {
        attribute: value;
        attributes: values;
    }

    selector - html element, class, id, to which style is applied
    attribute - property which is to be changed , color, font size, font, background, ....
    value - value of the attribute, 

    selector type -
        1. element selector - all the html elements, eg: h1, h2, body, p, table, ....... 

        2. class selector - user defined classes, 
        uses prefix dot (.) to apply css
        multiple classes can be used to apply css.
        
        3. id selector - user defined ids,
        uses prefix hash (#) to apply css 
        only one id is allowed/ only single id can be used to apply css.

    Priority: id > class > element


    CSS TYPES: 
        1. Internal CSS - same html file, in head section, using 'style' tag.
        2. Inline CSS - same html file, inside same tag, using 'style' attribute 
        3. External CSS - separate css file with extension '.css'. imported using link tag in html page in head section, no style keyword is required

    Priority: inline > (internal = external) 
    internal external whichever is defined at last
*/
